title._content: Putting the clothes out to dry under summer skies in Korea

description._content: ID number: HOBJ3364 Photographer: Phillip Oliver Hobson Date: 4 August 1952 Place: Korea Two unidentified men of the 3rd Battalion, The Royal Australian Regiment (3RAR), hanging out their washing to dry in the summer sun. Another soldier, holding a Bren light machine-gun, is squatting on their sandbagged dugout at rear. This front line trench on the top of a hill is typical of the defensive positions held by the Australians at the time. Rights Info: No known copyright restrictions. This photograph is from the Australian War Memorial's collection www.awm.gov.au Persistent URL: www.awm.gov.au/collection/HOBJ3364
